FBIS3-12375 "drnes040_k_94004" FBIS-NES-94-040 Document Type:Daily Report 1 Mar 1994 IRAQ Al-Majid Reportedly Moved From Amman After Surgery PM2502154994 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 25 Feb 94 p 2 PM2502154994 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Unattributed report: "A Hospital Is Sought To Treat Husayn Kamil"] [Text] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Iraqi sources have confirmed that Husayn Kamil Hasan al-Majid, the Iraqi president's son-in-law [and industry minister], has been moved from Jordan with a view to giving him intensive treatment after the first brain surgery he underwent 10 days ago. The sources believe al-Majid may end up in a Swiss hospital, as the French authorities refused to grant him an entry visa to their territory. The Iraqi Embassy in Amman sought to move the Iraqi president's son-in-law to Switzerland, Cuba, Romania, or Russia.
